news.title: Soon, daily camps to rectify disparity in property tax IDs in Gurugram
news.para: The decision was taken at the MCG House meeting on Monday after many councillors alleged that the representatives of the private agency contracted for carrying out the property tax survey in Gurgaon have been demanding money for making the corrections.

news.title: Cash-strapped Telangana takes land auction route to raise Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: Of this, about 900 crore is expected by selling Rajiv Swagruha flats at Bandlaguda near Nagole and Pocharam near Ghatkesar. The auction is now under way.

news.title: Delhi: Dusib to conduct survey, identify beneficiaries in slum areas for housing
news.para: The survey, said officials, will only be carried out on land belonging to Dusib. According to officials, there are over 7,000 hectares of encroached land under the agency’s jurisdiction where jhuggi jhopri clusters have come up.

news.title: Goa: GCZMA orders demolition of two illegal bungalows in CRZ
news.para: In the first case, the authority had received a complaint in 2020 stating that two bungalows of around 120sqm each have been constructed within the CRZ area at Betalbatim.

news.title: ED seeks details of cases, complaints against Ansal Group in Lucknow
news.para: Senior police officials said the ED would probe the allegations of money laundering against the real estate firm. Police have already provided details of 150 cases registered against the real estate firm.

news.title: NCDRC orders Dreamz Infra India to hand over flats, give 9% interest for delay
news.para: The home buyers had filed the “class-action” complaint against the Bengaluru-based Dreamz Infra India with the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (NCDRC) in 2019 seeking identical relief for all of them.

news.title: Gurugram: No work at site, DTCP orders FIR against Ocean Seven Buildtech
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP) has ordered the registration of an FIR against a city-based developer for failing to begin the construction of its affordable housing project in Sector 70 even three years after getting the licence.

news.title: Sebi imposes Rs 12 crore penalties on two Sahara Group firms, Subrata Roy & others
news.para: The case relates to the issuance of Optionally Fully Convertible Debentures (OFCDs) during 2008 and 2009 period by Sahara India Real Estate Corporation Limited (SIRECL), now known as Sahara Commodity Services Corporation Limited, and Sahara Housing Investment Corporation Limited (SHICL).

news.title: China Evergrande faces winding-up lawsuit in Hong Kong
news.para: Reeling under more than $300 billion in liabilities, Evergrande's offshore debt is deemed to be in default after missing payment obligations late last year.

news.title: Brigade Group signs JDA to develop 2.1 million sq ft in Chennai
news.para: The land, located at Perumbakkam, just off OMR Sholinganallur junction, is spread over 15 acres and will be developed as a large residential township.

news.title: TTK Prestige acquires over 40% stake in Ultrafresh Modular Solutions
news.para: TTK Prestige said that the business is well on its way to achieving double-digit growth. With this acquisition, the company is making an entry into the Rs 9,500 crore modular kitchen industry.

news.title: OMBR Layout: Court restores acquired land favouring Bengaluru development body
news.para: On March 31, 2016, a single bench held that physical possession of the land in question (about 2.5 acres) was not taken and hence, the acquisition had lapsed and section 24(2) of the new Land Acquisition Act (of 2013) would apply.

news.title: Pune civic body to start survey of STPs in big housing societies
news.para: The administration has given directives to housing complexes to treat sewage on their premises. Societies not operating treatment plants properly will be fined.

news.title: About 20 lakh buildings in Kerala were out of property tax net in 2021
news.para: Local bodies exempted 19.8 lakh residential buildings below 660sq ft from paying property tax in the state, accounting for 13% of total buildings as per the data collected in 2021.

news.title: Sebi to auction 23 properties of Utkarsha Plotters on July 29
news.para: ​The properties include agricultural land parcels, plots and residential spaces across Maharashtra, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.
